name: Arch Manning
summary: Recent news articles have focused on Arch Manning, the nephew of legendary quarterback Peyton Manning, and his decision to remain at the University of Texas despite being a backup quarterback. According to Peyton Manning, Arch has expressed contentment with his role behind starting quarterback Quinn Ewers and appreciates the opportunity to learn from him. Despite speculation about a potential transfer, Arch made his first career touchdown pass in Texas' rout of Colorado State. Texas head coach Steve Sarkisian praised both Manning and Ewers for their performances. Peyton Manning also shared that Arch is proud to be a Longhorn and has aspirations of becoming the team's future starting quarterback.
